Implemented the fix in:

- `src/generators/utils/parse.ts`

Changed the block delimiter regex used by `indexSitesFixesConfig()` so it only matches delimiter lines made of `==...`, instead of matching any `==` sequence inside CSS/base64 data URLs.

```ts
const delimiterRegex = /^[^\S\n]*={2,}[^\S\n]*$/gm;
```

This prevents padded base64 strings ending in `==` from being treated as config block separators.

Validation:
- Confirmed the new regex matches real delimiter lines and ignores the reported base64 padding case.
